         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">12/1/83 ¶  ¶ The pleasing duty devolves on me, honored Sir, to express my best thanks for your generosity of sending me a copy of your important volume "l'origine des plantes cultivées". ¶  It is a bo...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">83.01.12</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Alphonse de Candolle</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Bibliothèque des Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques, Geneva.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">12/1/83</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The pleasing duty devolves on me, honored Sir, to express my best thanks for your generosity of sending me a copy of your important volume "l'origine des plantes cultivées".<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">A. de Candolle (1882)<seg style="">.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> It is a book embracing a vast amount of research, and it is all the more valuable to us, as gift to science from you offered at a venerable age.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <name key="Oryza">Oryza</name> is doubtless indigenous to several parts of tropical Australia, and <name key="Indigofera%20tinctoria">Indigofera tinctoria</name> has been found in the virgin forests on the Endeavour-River,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Qld.</p>
               </note> where no Indigo-plantations exist.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I was anxious to place my homage for you on public record, and trust that the expressions in which I have done this, will be pleasing to you. The proof-sheet of the dedication from my new volume "systematic Census," was forwarded by last mail.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B83.03.04. M dedicated this work to G. Bentham, J. Hooker and A. de Candolle, 'who as heirs of great names worthily sustain world-wide ancestral fame, and who as leaders in phytography during more than a generation's time will be pre-eminent in biomorphic science through all ages'.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With deep veneration always your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Indigofera%20tinctoria">Indigofera tinctoria</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Oryza">Oryza</name>
            </p>
